translated: Benckert, Henric August, practicing physician, Gothenburg, born August 5, 1884 in Sundsvall to first city physician Carl Henric B. and Anna Sofia Åslund. Married for 12 years to Baroness Astrid Fock. Children: Brita, born in 1913, married from 1936-1946 to engineer J. Broberg in Gothenburg; Astrid, born in 1916, married to Bill C. Hodge in Los Angeles; Grieta, born in 1919, married to artist Torbjörn Zetterholm in Näsbypark; Nina, born in 1924, married to artist Sigfrid Södergren in Stockholm. Graduated from medical school in Stockholm in 1908, earned a medical license in Lund in 1913. Held various appointments at Lund Hospital, Karlstad Hospital surgical department, Sabbatsberg Hospital gynecology department, Allmänna BB in Stockholm, and Sahlgrenska Hospital maternity clinic. Currently an attending physician in Gothenburg and a field doctor in the military reserves. Authored several papers on gynecology and obstetrics. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa.
